Chang Wanquan, the Chinese defense minister and state councilor, met with U.S. Defense Secretary Chuck Hagel at the Pentagon on Monday morning. They discussed the two countries' military interaction at a time when U.S. foreign policy is supposed to shift its sights to southeast Asia. The two leaders came from a closed-door meeting where they likely discussed policies toward North Korea as well as Egypt, currently roiled in internal conflict.
